ion of issues at the heart of the emerging discipline of philosophy.A breathtaking work of intellectual history by one of today's most original classical scholars, The Philosophical Stage presents a novel approach to ancient drama and sets a path for a renewed understanding of early Greek thought.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aGreek dramaxHistory and criticism. 0aPhilosophy in literature. 7aDRAMA / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAeschylus.  aAntigone.  aAntiope.  aAristophanes.  aBacchae.  aElectra.  aEuripides.  aGorgias.  aGreek tragedy.  aMaria Michela Sassi.  aNietzsche.  aPalamedes.  aPhiloctetes.  aPlato.  aPresocratic philosophy.  aPrometheus.  aSimon Goldhill, Sophocles and the Language of Tragedy.  aSophocles.  aSuppliants.  aThe Beginnings of Philosophy in Greece.  athe Greek stage.  athe sophists.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishz978311075412408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073912140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691211114zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691211114423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691211114/original  a978-3-11-073912-1  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075412-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Liter